@node ICYMA "Icy Manipulator"

@{b}Icy Manipulator@{ub}

Color   = Colorless
Rarity  = A/B/UL(U) / IA(U)
Type    = Artifact
Cost    = 4
Artist  = Douglas Shuler (A/B/UL) / Amy Weber (IA)

@{b}NOTE@{ub}: The Ice Age card has different artwork. It also had
      Flavor Text added to the card's text.

Text(IA): <1T>: Tap target artifact, creature, or land.

Text(UL): <1T>: You may tap any land, creature, or artifact in play on
          either side. No effects are generated by the target card.

Text(AL): <1T>: You may tap any land, creature, or artifact in play on
          either side.

Flavor Text: @{i}"The scavengers who first found it called it the `Bone Crank.'
              Not a bad name, I'd say."
              ---Arcum Dagsson, Soldevi Machinist@{ui}

 @{" Rulings " link MTG_CARD_I.guide/ICYMA}

@endnode
@node ILLUS "Illusionary Mask"

@{b}Illusionary Mask@{ub}

Color   = Colorless
Rarity  = A/B/UL(R)
Type    = Artifact
Cost    = 2
Artist  = Amy Weber

Text(UL): <X>: You can summon a creature face down so opponent doesn't
          know what it is. The X cost can be any amount of mana, even 0;
          it serves to  hide the true casting cost of the creature, which
          you still have to spend. As soon as a face-down creature
          receives damage, deals damage, or is tapped, you must turn
          it face up.

 @{" Rulings " link MTG_CARD_I.guide/ILLMA}

@endnode
@node JADES "Jade Statue"

@{b}Jade Statue@{ub}

Color   = Colorless
Rarity  = A/B/UL(U)
Type    = Artifact (3/6)
Cost    = 4
Artist  = Dan Frazier

Text(UL): <2>: Jade Statue becomes a creature for the duration of the
          current attack exchange. Can be a creature only during an
          attack or defense.

Flavor Text: @{i}"Some of the other guys dared me to touch it, but
              I knew it weren't no ordinary hunk o' rock."
              ---Norin the Wary@{ui}

 @{" Rulings " link MTG_CARD_J.guide/JADES}

@endnode
